%% Diagram: Layout thrashing — interleaved reads/writes vs batched
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    autonumber
    participant JS as Main thread (JS)
    participant L as Layout engine

    Note over JS,L: Bad — interleaved reads and writes
    JS->>L: write style.width on item[0]
    Note over L: layout dirty
    JS->>L: read offsetWidth on item[1]
    L-->>JS: forces synchronous layout (1)
    JS->>L: write style.width on item[1]
    Note over L: layout dirty again
    JS->>L: read offsetWidth on item[2]
    L-->>JS: forces synchronous layout (2)
    JS->>L: write style.width on item[2]
    Note over L: layout dirty again
    JS->>L: read offsetWidth on item[3]
    L-->>JS: forces synchronous layout (3)

    Note over JS,L: Good — batch reads then batch writes
    JS->>L: read offsetWidth on item[0..N]
    L-->>JS: one synchronous layout (1)
    JS->>L: write style.width on item[0..N]
    Note over L: layout deferred to next frame
